# Polyptic ephemeral encrypted swap (POL-176). An installed box (install-to-disk.sh) carries a
# plain 4 GiB partition partlabelled POLYPTIC-SWAP; every boot, systemd-cryptsetup keys it with a
# FRESH random key from /dev/urandom, formats it as swap (the `swap` option), and discards the key
# at power-off. PRIVACY IS THE POINT: swapped pages can carry wall pixels and enrolment tokens, and
# with an ephemeral key nothing that hits this disk is ever readable again — the installed box stays
# as stateless as the diskless one it replaces.
#
# `nofail` keeps every OTHER boot clean: netboot/live boxes and pre-POL-176 installs have no such
# partition, and the by-partlabel path simply never appears — no degraded boot, no console noise.
polyptic-swap /dev/disk/by-partlabel/POLYPTIC-SWAP /dev/urandom swap,cipher=aes-xts-plain64,size=512,nofail
